<subSubSection id="E773FE391550E7D39B6331648FBC39F7" pageId="2" pageNumber="87" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6CE8399164A3FE255789652A944EFCC5" pageId="2" pageNumber="87">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="413539230219892F0C0414B2E0996C68" pageId="2" pageNumber="87">
<taxonomicName id="48D85BD9AC4880F4587A2F28F7FD8429" authorityName="M. A. Johnson" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyrtandra gregoryi" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gregoryi">
<emphasis id="E4B64265239238B4D146E683F8F12AF7" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="87">Cyrtandra gregoryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="66C5CC8D966BC08BF610EB7C8DC2FC4D" genus="C." lsidName="C. ciliata" pageId="2" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="ciliata">
<emphasis id="F86DF62A50FABF53C2BE8B4A411BCA76" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="87">C. ciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Seem. (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DAAAF8A89CBA8CF481D742EF0D18E0FF" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Cyrtandra gregoryi M. A. Johnson and closest relative (C. ciliata) based on a molecular phylogeny by Johnson et al. (2017). A C. gregoryi shrub habit B C. gregoryi corolla, anterior view C C. gregoryi flower, lateral view D C. gregoryi axillary cyme inflorescence E C. gregoryi adaxial leaf surface F C. ciliata corolla, anterior view G C. ciliata flower, lateral view H C. ciliata cauliflorous cyme inflorescence. All photos taken in the field by M. Johnson." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.91.21623.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174655" pageId="2" pageNumber="87">2</figureCitation>
), but differs in its elliptic to ovate leaves up to 39 
<normalizedToken id="6DA73AAF3937F48160538F5593A203D5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
17 cm (vs. lanceolate to ovate leaves up to 28 
<normalizedToken id="399FED9CF8D696A58414145E8D376E51" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12 cm), axillary inflorescences with indument of brown trichomes (vs. cauliflorous inflorescences with indument of white trichomes), pale green calyces 6-13 mm long that are cleft unequally into lanceolate coriaceous lobes (vs. calyces white, 7-10 mm long, cleft nearly to the base into equal linear-lanceolate lobes), these splitting along two to three sutures and recurving after anthesis (vs. remaining erect after anthesis), and corollas with exserted style and stamens (vs. style and stamens included).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
